column5: Went to my local trib today and got around like 60 or so fish, Thing is they were almost all minnow sized, even got a couple of suckers. Better than nothing i guess.         Heres a couple nice pics from a few days back...
nice upclose and personal shots.  Creek chubs are the rock bass of streams.
Whoa you are a pro bro.. when can you give me lessons?

Well.FF it looks like those little fellows kept you busy all day,the same happens where i go to my fav.little trib,i always end up donating about 40 or so roe bags to those hungry little trout & chubs & shinners,at least you got out to trib fish who would have thought you would be doing that on jan 1st......  cheers
Looks like u had fun man better then sittin at home i say. U going to have a smelt fry?? LOL
very nice! A few of those would make some real nice pike bait
